04/05/2005
SOFIA Bulgaria -- The defence ministry announced that two Bulgarian soldiers were killed Tuesday (3 May) when their jeep crashed in an Iraqi sandstorm. The accident occurred on a trip from Kuwait to a base in central Iraq. Bulgaria has a 450-strong contingent in Iraq but plans to reduce it by June and then pull out completely by year's end. (News.bg, Mediapool, Novinite - 03/05/05) 
